title: Virgin, Mother, Crone
description: Cybill goes out with a guy she meets on the freeway. Meanwhile, Rachel announces her pregnancy; Zoey goes out with an older guy; and Ira gets a shiny, new girlfriend.

title: How Can I Call You My Ex-Husbands If You Won't Go Away?
description: After learning there's a nude scene in her new film, Jeff moves in with Cybill and Ira tries to rekindle his romance with her. Meanwhile, Maryann discovers her ex-husband, Dr. Dick, is sleeping with another woman.

title: As the World Turns to Crap
description: Cybill learns that either she or Andrea will lose their soap opera job, so the two go to war. Meanwhile, Kevin's parents come to visit and announce he and Rachel are moving to Boston.

title: Look Who's Stalking
description: Maryann befriends Dr. Dick's new girlfriend. Meanwhile, Cybill discovers she's dating Ira's ex-psychiatrist.

title: Starting on the Wrong Foot
description: Jonathan Frakes tries to get a date with Cybill. Meanwhile, Zoey vows chastity; and Maryann behaves insanely following a blind date.

title: Call Me Irresponsible
description: Maryann and Cybill go to Las Vegas to max out Dr. Dick's credit card. Meanwhile, Ira babysits Zoey; and Jeff gets poison oak.

title: See Jeff Jump, Jump, Jeff, Jump!
description: Jeff decides to give up his career as a stuntman, so Cybill tracks down his mentor to change his mind. Meanwhile, Maryann becomes engrossed in the O.J. Simpson murder trial.

title: The Curse of Zoey
description: After speaking with a psychic, Maryann becomes convinced Ira is her soulmate and Zoey is a dark cloud hanging over Cybill's life.

title: The Replacements
description: When Maryann starts dating again, Cybill tries to reconnect with family and old friends.

title: Death and Execs
description: Following a near death experience, Cybill decides to rekindle her romance with Ira.

title: The Last Temptation of Cybill
description: Every female around has eyes for Cybill's hunky new costar Rick, but he only has eyes for Cybill. Meanwhile, Jeff discovers Rachel's left her husband.

title: The Big Sleep-Over
description: Ira flips out when Zoey's new boyfriend spends the night. Meanwhile, Maryann goes on a trip with Bob and winds up at the alter with another man.

title: The Cheese Stands Alone
description: Cybill gets a job on a cheesy sitcom; Maryann throws a party concurrent with a party thrown by her ex; Ira's book gets optioned for a film; Jeff's band gets a gig.

title: Cybill Discovers the Meaning of Life
description: Cybill drags Maryann to the desert for a spiritual quest. Meanwhile Rachel goes into labor.

title: Zing!
description: Maryann sets Cybill up with her lawyer, but Cybill's far more interested in his father.

title: Since I Lost My Baby
description: Cybill discovers Jeff's ex is pregnant with his baby. Meanwhile, Maryann loses Rachel's baby at a boutique.

title: Cybill with an 'S'
description: Cybill and Maryann make the shocking discovery that Ira's girlfriend has multiple personalities. Meanwhile, Zoey falls for a busboy.

title: Cybill's Fifteen Minutes
description: Cybill haplessly gets caught in a sex scandal with a Hollywood director.

title: Nice Work If You Can Get It
description: Cybill takes a job as a waitress to pay back money to Maryann. Meanwhile, Zoey tells her parents she's taken a job at Burger Barn.

title: To Sir, with Lust
description: Cybill goes out with her acting teacher; Zoey makes out with Sean; Ira gets writer's block; Maryann and Dr. Dick's war escalates.

title: They Shoot Turkeys, Don't They?
description: Everyone has plans for Thanksgiving: Ira and Jeff go camping, Rachel's bound for Boston, Maryann expects a visit from Justin, Zoey makes plans with Sean, and Cybill is forced to work with a tyrannical prepubescent costar.

title: Local Hero
description: Cybill meets her Russian fans. Meanwhile Rachel makes Ira face his fears and Kevin turns to Cybill for marital advice.

title: The Odd Couples
description: Ira sees Maryann as his lunatic muse; Cybill bonds with Sean; Cybill's new neighbor begins stealing from her.

title: Mourning Has Broken
description: Cybill decides to resume dating David, but Maryann becomes convinced he murdered his wife. Meanwhile, Zoey enlists Rachel to accompany her on a Mexican road trip to secretly repair Cybill's car.

title: The Big Apple Can Bite Me
description: The ladies whisk Cybill off to New York for her birthday, leaving the guys alone with the babies.

title: Educating Zoey
description: Cybill and Ira attend career day at Zoey's school. Meanwhile, Maryann buys a pro-boxer.

title: Where's Zoey?
description: Zoey rebels by vanishing, sending Cybill and Maryann on a wild goose chase to find her. Meanwhile, Ira tries to pass off a prostitute as his new love interest, and Cybill stars in a corny superhero show.

title: Lowenstein's Lament
description: When Ira's book gets made into a film, Paula Abdul is cast and the story is drastically altered. Meanwhile, Zoey gets a job working in an art gallery.

title: A Who's Who for What's His Name
description: After Cybill fires her agent, he drops dead, so she reluctantly agrees to make his funeral arrangements. Meanwhile, Maryann attempts to seduce Ira.

title: Wedding Bell Blues
description: Cybill and Maryann decide to sabotage Dr. Dick's wedding to Cybill's nemesis, Andrea.

title: Romancing the Crone
description: Cybill opens up her home to an eccentric old Hollywood actress; Zoey discovers the guy she's been cyber-taunting is Kevin; Ira works as a garbage man to research his latest novel; Maryann schemes to destroy Dr. Dick's new marriage.

title: An Officer and a Thespian
description: Cybill steals a squad car and impersonates a cop. Meanwhile, Kevin hosts a party for his colleagues and Zoey tries to fix up Ira.

title: Virgin, Mother, Cheater
description: Convinced that Kevin is having an affair, Rachel contemplates cheating on him with her mechanic. Cybill and Maryann arrive at the motel in time to prevent a disastrous misunderstanding - Kevin is actually distracted by his failure to gain tenure - but discover Sean, Zoey's boyfriend, getting ice for the girl he's cheating with. Kevin and Rachel agree to work on saving their relationship; Zoey tells Sean to get out of her life.

title: When You're Hot, You're Hot
description: Cybill begins experiencing pre-menopausal symptoms. Meanwhile Ira's mother comes to visit and he soon realizes she's become a different person; and a horse wanders into Cybill's back yard.

title: Pal Zoey
description: Following her breakup, Zoey bonds with Cybill. Meanwhile, Maryann tries to make Ira jealous by leading him to believe she's having a fling with Cybill's visiting redneck cousin Lyle.

title: Three Women and a Dummy
description: Maryann and Ira have a disastrous first date; Zoey goes to prom with the most popular guy in school; Cybill hangs out with her favorite waiter.

title: Going Out with a Bang
description: Cybill gets a job as a clown on The Major Milo Show and has to fend off the advances of the star. Meanwhile Zoey graduates, Rachel tries to relive her childhood and Maryann and Ira attempt to have sex.

title: Bringing Home the Bacon
description: Cybill steals a pig from her TV show. Meanwhile, Ira and Maryann have an awkward sexual encounter, Kevin loses his job and Zoey returns from Europe and announces she's moving out.

title: Venice or Bust
description: Cybill takes a sculpting class; Maryann and Ira realize they're incompatible, Zoey moves out; Rachel and Kevin move in.

title: Cybill and Maryann Go to Japan
description: On their trip to Japan, Cybill and Maryann liberate an oppressed Japanese woman. Meanwhile, Ira tries to get Sean and Zoey back together.

title: It's for You, Mrs. Lincoln
description: Cybill's debut as an understudy doesn't go off without a hitch. Meanwhile, Maryann and Ira have trouble being hospitable after their breakup; Kevin and Rachel continue to quarrel and Zoey's roommate moves out.

title: Cybill, Get Your Gun
description: After Cybill's home is burglarized she turns to Vicki Lawrence for self defense tips. Meanwhile, Maryann is a prime suspect when Dr. Dick goes missing; and Jeff drags Ira to an AA meeting to pick up women.

title: Cybill Does Diary
description: Stunned to see her own face transposed onto another actress' body for the cover of a porn video - [I]The Last Picture Ho[/I] - Cybill marches off to complain to the distributor, only for her and Maryann to be challenged to produce their own erotic script within one week. Unfortunately, Ira e-mails the wrong file - and Zoey's memoir of losing her virginity in Italy nearly hits the screen.

title: Sex, Drugs and Catholicism
description: Ira asks Holly to marry him. Maryann revisits her Catholic upbringing. Cybill blows a fuse when Holly suggests Zoey should underplay her own intelligence rather than break up with the co-worker she's just started dating.

title: Going to Hell in a Limo: Part 1
description: Cybill gets cast on a new sci-fi show, but her smug costar plots to push her out of the picture. Meanwhile, Zoey hosts a bridal shower for Ira's fiance.

title: Going to Hell in a Limo: Part 2
description: Cybill tries to find an angle when her costar fires the show's chauvinistic head writer. Meanwhile Zoey decides she doesn't want to be in Ira's wedding.

title: Buffalo Gals
description: Maryann goes to Buffalo for her high school reunion and discovers her son's been living with her parents.

title: A Hell of a Christmas
description: Cybill's mother comes for a visit and accuses her of favoring Zoey over Rachel.

title: The Little Drummer Girls
description: The ladies indulge in a full moon cleansing ritual. Meanwhile Ira discovers Sean cheated on Zoey.

title: Bachelor Party
description: Cybill and Maryann disguise themselves as men when Ira's bachelor party is moved to a strip club.

title: Little Bo Peep
description: Cybill's job is jeopardized when she's mauled by a sheep on TV. Meanwhile she dates a man who's too good to be true; Maryann falls for a vet who has the same name as her ex and Ira finds himself with nothing to do after his breakup.

title: In Her Dreams
description: Cybill is plagued by bizarre dreams after she's fired from her show. Meanwhile, Ira is audited by the IRS, Kevin gets a job teaching 3rd graders and Maryann gets a mammogram.

title: Valentine's Day
description: Maryann spends Valentine's Day with her son and boyfriend. Meanwhile Cybill becomes known as "The Condom Queen" after starring in a series of condom commercials and Zoey moves back in.

title: Kiss Me, You Fool
description: Jeff gets Cybill a job as the leading lady in his new film, but problems arise when they have to kiss.

title: True Confessions
description: Cybill realizes Ira subconsciously modeled the character in his new play on Maryann, so she begins stalking her for character inspiration. Meanwhile Zoey lands a small supporting role in the play too.

title: Name That Tune
description: Cybill tries to live down the role of Patty the Potty by singing on "Name That Tune." Meanwhile, Rachel breaks her leg having sex, and Maryann fears she's pregnant.

title: From Boca, with Love
description: When Richard asks to meet Maryann's mother, she tries to pass off Ira's as her own. Meanwhile Zoey applies for college and a handsome fan who asks out Cybill turns out to be a toothless dud.

title: All of Me
description: Cybill flips out when her body is drastically altered on a billboard campaign. Meanwhile, Ira gives up coffee, and Zoey starts dating Justin.

title: The Wedding
description: Cybill's family attends a wedding; Justin coaxes Zoey into dancing; Maryann and Richard visit her parents.

title: The Piano
description: Cybill reluctantly sucks up to Andrea to ensure Zoey gets a prestigious music audition.

title: There Was an Old Woman
description: Ira pursues Zoey's piano teacher; Cybill relentlessly pursues a director for a part; and Richard proposes to Maryann.

title: Mother's Day
description: Cybill's mother comes to visit and gets her feelings hurt when she overhears her daughter telling Maryann that she doesn't want to be anything like her mother.

title: Let's Stalk
description: Cybill gets a shot at hosting a cooking segment on "Wake Up L.A.", but only if the audience prefers it to a book review segment hosted by Ira. Maryann sets a date for her marriage to Richard, and in lieu of a bachelorette party, she and the girls decide to exact one last act of revenge on her ex, Dr. Dick. While skulking around outside Dr. Dick's house, she finds out Dick and Amanda are on the outs, giving rise to second thoughts about marrying Richard. Cybill has a disturbing dream.

title: Regarding Henry
description: Cybill has erotic dreams about Richard so she visits a past life regression therapist. Meanwhile Justin and Zoey make plans to have sex, and Maryann considers taking back Dr. Dick.

title: The Love of Her Life
description: Cybill rekindles her romance with a director she fell for 27 years earlier. Meanwhile, Maryann mistakes Justin's gift for a hideous necklace and Ira takes up basketball.

title: The Big, Flouncy Thing
description: Zoey insists on buying a ridiculous dress for her piano recital. Meanwhile, Cybil picks up a guy at the department store.

title: Some Like It Hot
description: Cybil makes everyone crazy with her menopause.

title: Like Family
description: Cybill must deal with an out-of-control teenage co-star and the hurt feelings of her best friend.

title: Earthquake
description: Cybill decides an earthquake is the universe's way of telling her to quit her crummy sitcom job.

title: Halloween
description: Cybill hosts the Halloween PBS pledge drive. Meanwhile, Dr. Dick tries to win back Maryann; and Zoey and Justin decide to see other people.

title: Where's a Harpoon When You Need One?
description: Dr. Dick uses a love letter to drive a wedge between Cybill and Maryann.

title: How to Get a Head in Show Business
description: Cybill meets Minnie, an obsessed fan who stole a replica of Cybill's head from a wax museum. Meanwhile, Zoey decides to give up her music career.

title: Grandbaby
description: Rachel gives birth to her second child. Meanwhile, Maryann has her appendix out and tensions rise when Jeff makes a move on Cybill.

title: The Golden Years
description: Several decades in the future, Cybill and Maryann reflect on a past dating failure.

title: Show Me the Minnie
description: Cybill applies for a bank loan to repair her garage. Meanwhile, obsessed fan Minnie trashes Cybill on a cable access show; and Maryann and Ira have a huge fight.

title: Bakersfield
description: After Cybill's mother dies, she finds an unsent letter and decides to track down its intended recipient.

title: Once, Twice, Three Times a Lady
description: Cybill gets a visit from and old boyfriend who happened to be her first time. Just as she thinks everything is perfect with her visitor, she gets a nasty surprise and it turns out Mr Perfect isn't so perfect.

title: Cybill Sheridan's Day Off
description: When Maryann and Dr. Dick resume their war, Cybill is mistakenly drugged, kidnapped and dumped at the bus station in a nightie.

title: Fine Is Not a Feeling
description: Maryann seeks therapy when Justin gets a job in San Francisco.

title: Oh Brother!
description: Cybill's niece comes to visit and the ladies decide to kidnap Ira for his birthday.

title: Whose Wife Am I, Anyway?
description: Oblivious to their divorce, Jeff's grandmother arrives to celebrate their 25th anniversary, but complications arise when the waiter introduces Cybill as his own girlfriend to his parents. Meanwhile, Maryann delivers a calf.

title: Dream Date
description: Cybill's obnoxious blind date saves Ira's mother's life.

title: Farewell, My Sweet
description: Cybill discovers she's allergic to chocolate. Meanwhile, Maryann's parents drop in unannounced.

title: Daddy
description: Cybill's father orchestrates a morning show interview for his daughter, but he has ulterior motives.

title: Don Gianni
description: The first man Zoey slept with arrives from Italy to visit her.

title: Cybill in the Morning
description: Cybill gets a job hosting a morning show, but she soon finds herself at war with both the co-host and producer.

title: Ka-Boom!
description: Dr. Dick swindles Maryann out of her life's savings, so she retaliates by blowing up his property. Meanwhile, Cybill's morning show gets canceled.
